<TITLE> 119 cases filed against alleged war criminals: Shafiq </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June25 (bdnews24.com)As many as 119 cases have been filed against alleged war criminals including Jamaat-e-Islami chief Matiur Rahman Nizami across the country, the law minister told the parliament on Wednesday. A total of 1,522 people stand accused of war crimes in those cases, 1,000 of them unnamed. Law minister Shafique Ahmed gave the information in response to a question from Zakir Hossain, MP of Kurigram-4, in the morning session presided over by deputy speaker Shawkat Ali. Two cases have been filed against Nizami in Pallabi and Keraniganj police stations. Genocide, arson, rape and looting were perpetrated by local collaborators of Pakistan army during the war of independence from Pakistan in 1971. Seventy people have been arrested in 119 cases. Among the arrestees 57 were granted bail and the rest have been detained in prison, the minister added. bd
